@startuml sequence-generate-report
!theme plain

title Power Atlas -- Sequence: Engineer Generates PDF Report
caption Engineer requests a project report, system generates PDF via ReportLab server

skinparam sequenceArrowColor #444444
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #555555
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #FFF3E0
skinparam noteBorderColor #888888

actor "Power Engineer" as eng
participant "Frontend\n(Vite + JS)" as fe
participant "Nginx\n(443)" as nginx
participant "Flask API\n(8000)" as api
participant "Auth Module" as auth
participant "Report Generator" as report
participant "Project Engine" as proj
participant "Calculation Engine" as calc
database "SQLite DB" as db
participant "PDF Server\n(ReportLab)\nport 5020" as pdf
collections "Static Files\n/public/reports/" as files

== Step 1: Engineer Requests Report ==

eng -> fe : Open project "Al-Riyadh Office Tower"\nClick "Generate PDF Report"\nSelect options: full report, include layout

fe -> nginx : POST /api/reports/generate\nAuthorization: Bearer <JWT>\n{\n  "project_id": 47,\n  "report_type": "full",\n  "include_sections": [\n    "summary",\n    "load_schedule",\n    "calculations",\n    "generator_sizing",\n    "layout",\n    "appendix"\n  ],\n  "format": "pdf"\n}
nginx -> api : Proxy to 8000

== Step 2: Authenticate and Authorize ==

api -> auth : Verify JWT token
auth -> db : SELECT * FROM sessions\nWHERE session_token = ?\nAND is_active = true\nAND expires_at > NOW()
db --> auth : Valid session (user_id: 12)
auth --> api : Authorized (engineer role)

== Step 3: Gather Project Data ==

api -> report : Generate report for project 47
report -> proj : Fetch complete project data

proj -> db : SELECT p.*, c.client_name, c.email\nFROM projects p\nLEFT JOIN clients c ON p.client_id = c.client_id\nWHERE p.project_id = 47
db --> proj : Project with client info

proj -> db : SELECT * FROM loads\nWHERE project_id = 47\nORDER BY load_type, load_name
db --> proj : 3 load records

proj -> db : SELECT * FROM generators
db --> proj : Generator catalog

proj -> db : SELECT * FROM project_activity\nWHERE project_id = 47\nORDER BY created_at DESC
db --> proj : Activity log

proj --> report : Complete project dataset

== Step 4: Run Final Calculations ==

report -> calc : Calculate report figures

calc -> calc : **Connected Load Summary:**\nHVAC Chillers: 4 x 150 = 600 kW\nLighting LP-01: 1 x 45 = 45 kW\nUPS Systems: 2 x 80 = 160 kW\n---\nTotal Connected: 805 kW / 947.06 kVA\n\n**Demand Analysis:**\nDemand Load: 805 x 0.80 = 644 kW\nDiversified: 644 x 0.70 = 450.8 kW\n\n**Generator Sizing:**\nRequired: 450.8 kW + 20% margin\nRecommended: 550 kW generator\nMatch: CAT C15 (500 kW) -- undersized\nMatch: CAT C18 (600 kW) -- suitable\n\n**Critical Load Analysis:**\nCritical loads: 760 kW\n(HVAC + UPS marked critical)

calc --> report : All calculations and\nrecommendations

== Step 5: Generate PDF via ReportLab Server ==

report -> report : Assemble report payload\nwith all data sections

report -> pdf : POST http://localhost:5020/generate\nContent-Type: application/json\n{\n  "template": "full_project_report",\n  "filename": "PRN-2026-00047_report.pdf",\n  "data": {\n    "project": {name, prn, client, ...},\n    "loads": [{...}, {...}, {...}],\n    "totals": {connected, demand, diversified},\n    "generators": {recommended: "CAT C18"},\n    "layout_data": {svg_snapshot: "..."},\n    "activity_log": [{...}]\n  },\n  "options": {\n    "page_size": "A4",\n    "include_cover": true,\n    "include_toc": true,\n    "company_logo": true\n  }\n}

note over pdf
  **ReportLab PDF Server Processing:**
  1. Parse JSON payload
  2. Load A4 page template
  3. Render cover page with logo & project info
  4. Render table of contents
  5. Render executive summary section
  6. Render load schedule table
  7. Render calculation details with formulas
  8. Render generator sizing recommendation
  9. Render layout diagram (from Konva export)
  10. Render appendix with activity log
  11. Add page numbers, headers, footers
  12. Write PDF to output path
end note

pdf -> pdf : ReportLab generates PDF\n(~2-5 seconds for full report)

pdf -> files : Write file:\n/public/reports/PRN-2026-00047_report.pdf\n(~850 KB)
files --> pdf : File written

pdf --> report : 200 OK\n{\n  "status": "success",\n  "filename": "PRN-2026-00047_report.pdf",\n  "file_size": 872448,\n  "pages": 12\n}

== Step 6: Log Activity and Respond ==

report -> db : INSERT INTO project_activity\n(project_id: 47, user_id: 12,\naction_type: 'report_generated',\ndescription: 'Full PDF report generated\n(12 pages, 852 KB)')
db --> report : Activity logged

report --> api : Report ready
api --> nginx : 200 OK\n{\n  "status": "success",\n  "report": {\n    "filename": "PRN-2026-00047_report.pdf",\n    "download_url": "/reports/PRN-2026-00047_report.pdf",\n    "pages": 12,\n    "file_size_kb": 852,\n    "generated_at": "2026-03-05T14:23:17Z"\n  }\n}
nginx --> fe : Response

fe -> fe : Show success notification\nwith download button
fe --> eng : "Report generated (12 pages)\n[Download PDF]"

== Step 7: Engineer Downloads Report ==

eng -> fe : Click "Download PDF"
fe -> nginx : GET /reports/PRN-2026-00047_report.pdf
nginx -> files : Serve static file
files --> nginx : PDF binary (852 KB)
nginx --> fe : Content-Type: application/pdf\n(852 KB file)
fe --> eng : Browser downloads\nPRN-2026-00047_report.pdf

@enduml
